# TodoMVC Rust — Architecture Plan

## Overview
Full-stack Rust TodoMVC: Leptos CSR frontend (Trunk) + Axum backend + SQLite.

## Project Structure
```
Cargo.toml              # workspace: members = ["frontend", "server"]
rust-toolchain.toml     # stable + wasm32-unknown-unknown
frontend/
  Cargo.toml            # leptos, gloo-net, serde, leptos_router
  Trunk.toml
  index.html            # TodoMVC shell + CSS links
  css/                  # todomvc-common, todomvc-app-css
  src/
    main.rs             # App component, router setup, mount
    api.rs              # HTTP client (gloo-net) for REST calls
    state.rs            # Reactive signals: todos, filter, editing
    components/
      mod.rs
      header.rs         # New todo input
      todo_item.rs      # Single todo (view + edit mode)
      todo_list.rs      # Filtered list + toggle-all
      footer.rs         # Count, filters, clear completed
server/
  Cargo.toml            # axum, sqlx, serde, tokio, tower-http
  src/
    main.rs             # Axum app, static file serving, DB init
    db.rs               # SQLite pool setup, migrations
    models.rs           # Todo struct, CreateTodo, UpdateTodo, etc.
    routes.rs           # REST handlers: CRUD + bulk ops
  tests/
    api_tests.rs        # Integration tests (in-memory SQLite)
migrations/
  YYYYMMDD_create_todos.sql
.github/workflows/ci.yml
```

## Key Design Decisions
- **No shared crate**: Server-side models duplicated minimally in frontend (serde types in api.rs/state.rs). Keeps wasm compilation simple.
- **CSR-only Leptos**: No SSR. Trunk builds WASM, Axum serves static files + API.
- **Hash-based routing**: `#/`, `#/active`, `#/completed` via leptos_router.
- **SQLite via sqlx**: Compile-time query checking where possible. Auto-run migrations on startup.
- **gloo-net**: HTTP client for frontend API calls (fetch-based, wasm-compatible).

## Dependency Chain
```
#1 (workspace)
  → #2 (Leptos/Trunk)
    → #3 (Axum server)
    → #4 (TodoMVC CSS)
    → #9 (API client)
      → #10 (state/signals)
        → #11 (Header), #12 (TodoItem), #14 (Footer)
          → #13 (TodoList, depends on #12)
          → #15 (Editing, depends on #12)
            → #16 (Routing, depends on #14)
              → #17 (Assembly, depends on #15, #16)
                → #19 (Frontend tests)
                → #21 (README)
  → #5 (SQLite/migrations, depends on #3)
    → #6 (Models)
      → #7 (CRUD endpoints)
        → #8 (Bulk endpoints)
          → #18 (Backend tests)
            → #20 (CI)
```

## REST API
- GET    /api/todos              → Vec<Todo>
- POST   /api/todos              → Todo  (body: {title})
- PATCH  /api/todos/:id          → Todo  (body: {title?, completed?})
- DELETE /api/todos/:id          → 204
- PATCH  /api/todos              → 204   (body: {completed: bool}) — toggle all
- DELETE /api/todos/completed    → 204   — clear completed

## Todo Schema
```sql
CREATE TABLE todos (
  id TEXT PRIMARY KEY,
  title TEXT NOT NULL,
  completed BOOLEAN NOT NULL DEFAULT FALSE,
  display_order INTEGER NOT NULL
);
```
